secrets.quote: Three may keep a secret, if two of them are dead.
secrets.author: Benjamin Franklin

secrets.quote: If you want to keep a secret, you must also hide it from yourself.
secrets.author: George Orwell

secrets.quote: Secrets, silent, stony sit in the dark palaces of both our hearts: secrets weary of their tyranny: tyrants willing to be dethroned.
secrets.author: James Joyce

secrets.quote: We dance round in a ring and suppose, but the secret sits in the middle and knows.
secrets.author: Robert Frost

statements.sentence: It is never too late to learn.
